snippet.textDisplay:
Caroline may be gone but will never be forgotten by all the people whose lives she has touched throughout her career. It is really sad to see such a person with great potential has had her life taken away from her just like that. It is unfortunate that we are living in a society full of greedy, selfish and ignorant individuals. Because of this, they just follow the crowd without analysing what impact their actions could have on others.
The blame always go to social media, forgetting that social media is us, without us, social media does not exist. We all need to develop a sense of responsibility and duty of care for each other. We should all initiate change in ourselves, which social media won’t give us but it will get worse if we fail to pay any attention to what is going on around us. Whoever participated in driving Caroline to death will live with the guilt and will be haunted for as long as they live.
I would not blame Megan and Harry for stepping down from their duties and leaving the country. This is exactly what they are running away from, to protect their lives and live it according to their wish before it is too late. As much as we all know, nothing can be done to bring Caroline back, but we can all join hands and stand against this kind of behaviour, which is totally unacceptable.
This kind of behaviour is common in work places due to the “I don’t care attitude,” where nobody seems to mind blaming the victim. Fairness and honesty and respect are far from near. Let us learn from the past experiences and from such incidents to bring change in us. We all need to develop and embrace a culture where we care for each other and stand for what is right to make this world a better place for all of us.
